    <body>
      <section eId="sec_580_612">
        <num>580-612</num>
        <heading>Recognition of order modified in another state</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_612__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>may enforce its order that was modified only as to arrears and\ninterest accruing before the modification;\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_612__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>may provide appropriate relief for violations of its order which\noccurred before the effective date of the modification; and\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_580_612__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>shall recognize the modifying order of the other state, upon\nregistration, for the purpose of enforcement.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
